<br>
Those disciplines were given to us in an era when AC meant something. Even at the end of Kunark the most uber warriors (i.e. Me and a small handful of others) could barely reach the AC softcap, a cap which was never raised in Velious and only marginally increased in SoL - over two years later. Conversely, the average fight times versus uber mobs were raised almost exponentially while the DPM from mobs barely changed; and in MANY Velious and even Luclin uber encounters, remained BELOW the DPM of Dragons in Veeshan's Peak - the Vision took a wicked, wicked wrong turn in game design. How could they have not seen this mess coming?<br>
<br>
In those days, the term monk and tank were only used in the same sentence when you were talking about what it felt like to get rolled over by a twenty ton tank if you were a monk that tried to tackle anything larger than a bread box, head on.<br>
<br>
Additionally, due to the fact that fights hardly ever lasted more than 4-5 minutes, the disciplines made sense - two years ago.<br>
<br>
Right now they are only a vestige; a remnant of a bygone era: A time when Armor Class meant something and the warrior class was more than a mish mash of bad coding and lost grey matter.<br>
<br>
Are you a fish because you had gills once?<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufrodlin7th.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Frodlin7th</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/8/02 7:51:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=907.topic&index=411>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   rofl</span><hr size=1> You know, <br>
<br>
Let's see if I can make this easy enough for even our new Paladin friends to understand.<br>
<br>
You seem to think that....<br>
<br>
Having the same AC as warriors is ok<br>
<br>
Having approximately 90% of the HP as a warrior is OK<br>
<br>
Having the same defensive skill as warriors is OK<br>
<br>
Having AA skills which brings you closer to warriors' ability is OK<br>
<br>
Having superior weapons which brings your melee DPS so close to warriors that it's insignificant is OK<br>
<br>
Basically, what you're saying is that you want the line between Paladins and Warriors to be so thin in terms of melee that it's barely recognizable at all.<br>
<br>
I would be ok with that<br>
<br>
-IF-<br>
<br>
You didn't have the same manapool as casters<br>
<br>
You didn't have LoH<br>
<br>
You didn't have the ability to recover from solo fights at 4x the rate of warriors.<br>
<br>
You didn't have the ability to create situations where while soloing, it's always you +mob, and any adds can be rooted safely out of melee range<br>
<br>
You didn't have server numbers which allowed you to be equiped on items which are class or 2class specific at a rate which is 10x faster than any others.<br>
<br>
You didn't have a free resurrection so that soloing is without any risk whatsoever.<br>
<br>
Incredibly enough, Paladins are the second or third best healers in the game.  In an exp group, a Paladin is a wiser choice than a druid for healing because a Paladin can correct larger problems fast using LoH, whereas a druid cannot, EVER.  If something goes a little wrong in a group setting, the Paladin is ALWAYS the better groupmate, even if they're not doing the primary tanking.<br>
<br>
So, what I'm getting at is that you guys really DO &quot;have it all&quot; and you're sitting here wagging your finger at us, who have given up any right to ALL of that which has been described above and in return we have gotten.....nothing, we've gotten told by you guys that we should be easily replaceable by you guys, that Everquest should be easier for you to play than us, because once upon a time, when Kunark was the latest, you couldn't get a group in Sebilis over a warrior and had to /lfg, and because once upon a time /disc defensive was really powerful.<br>
<br>
What you're saying is that your paranoia over being the CLEAR 2nd choice for a tank, we should simply bend over and take it.   Paladins SHOULD suffer some penalty, enough to make a difference in both areas of their existence, in melee AND in casting, for the benefit of having both.  Paladins seem to be the ONLY class that I've ever seen who says &quot;Well, we can get aggro without effort and we should not have to worry if we do&quot;.<br>
